<subSubSection pageId="301" pageNumber="302" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="301" pageNumber="302">
Bulirsch (2009: 19) reported that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kult" authorityYear="1950" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="301" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weyrauchi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Dyschirius weyrauchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kult, described from one specimen collected in Peru in 1900, is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1857" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="301" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrocerus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Dyschirius erythrocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. If this synonymy is correct, then the specimen from Peru is probably mislabeled.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
